                </div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Driveway Extensions</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Add parking space for additional vehicles, boats, or RVs with seamless concrete that matches your existing driveway.</p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-trust/10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-trust" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17.66 7.93L12 2.27 6.34 7.93c-3.12 3.12-3.12 8.19 0 11.31C7.9 20.8 9.95 21.58 12 21.58c2.05 0 4.1-.78 5.66-2.34 3.12-3.12 3.12-8.19 0-11.31zM12 19.59c-1.6 0-3.11-.62-4.24-1.76C6.62 16.69 6 15.19 6 13.59s.62-3.11 1.76-4.24L12 5.1v14.49z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Driveway Resurfacing</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Restore worn driveways with a new overlay that covers imperfections and provides a fresh, clean surface.</p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-secondary/10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-secondary" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22.7 19l-9.1-9.1c.9-2.3.4-5-1.5-6.9-2-2-5-2.4-7.4-1.3L9 6 6 9 1.6 4.7C.4 7.1.9 10.1 2.9 12.1c1.9 1.9 4.6 2.4 6.9 1.5l9.1 9.1c.4.4 1 .4 1.4 0l2.3-2.3c.5-.4.5-1.1.1-1.4z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Crack Repair & Patching</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Fix cracks and damaged sections before they spread. Proper repair extends your driveway's lifespan significantly.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-dark mt-10 mb-4">Why Concrete is the Best Choice for Florida Driveways</h3>
            
            <p>When it comes to driveway materials in Florida, concrete offers unmatched advantages over alternatives like asphalt or pavers. Here's why homeowners throughout Volusia County consistently choose concrete:</p>
            
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 my-6">
              <li><strong>Durability in Florida Heat:</strong> Unlike asphalt that softens in intense summer heat, concrete maintains its structural integrity even on the hottest days. You won't have to worry about tire marks, indentations, or surface deterioration from UV exposure.</li>
              <li><strong>Lower Lifetime Cost:</strong> While the initial cost may be slightly higher than asphalt, concrete requires less maintenance and lasts nearly twice as long. Over a 30-year period, concrete is significantly more economical.</li>
              <li><strong>Minimal Maintenance:</strong> Concrete driveways need only occasional cleaning and sealing every 3-5 years. Asphalt requires regular sealing every 1-3 years to prevent deterioration.</li>
              <li><strong>Design Flexibility:</strong> With stamped patterns, colored concrete, and exposed aggregate options, you can achieve virtually any look – from natural stone to brick to modern minimalist designs.</li>
              <li><strong>Increased Property Value:</strong> A well-maintained concrete driveway adds curb appeal and value to your home, making it an investment that pays dividends if you ever decide to sell.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-dark mt-10 mb-4">Our Driveway Installation Process</h3>
            
            <p>Quality concrete work starts long before the truck arrives. Here's what makes our driveway installations stand out:</p>
            
            <div class="bg-primary/5 p-6 rounded-xl my-8 not-prose">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-secondary-dark">Step 1: Site Preparation</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">We excavate to the proper depth (typically 8-10 inches), grade for proper drainage away from your home, and install a compacted gravel base. This foundation work is crucial for preventing settling and cracking.</p>
              
              <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-secondary-dark">Step 2: Forms & Reinforcement</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Wooden or metal forms are installed to create clean edges and maintain proper thickness. We add fiber mesh, wire mesh, or rebar reinforcement depending on your driveway's requirements.</p>
              
              <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-secondary-dark">Step 3: Concrete Placement</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">We use high-quality 4,000 PSI concrete delivered by truck. The pour is carefully managed to ensure consistent coverage and proper consolidation to eliminate air pockets.</p>
              
              <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-secondary-dark">Step 4: Finishing</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Our experienced finishers smooth the surface, add control joints to manage cracking, apply any decorative treatments, and create the texture you've chosen – from smooth to broom-finish to stamped patterns.</p>
              
              <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-secondary-dark">Step 5: Curing & Cleanup</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600">Proper curing is essential for maximum strength. We apply curing compound or cover the concrete to retain moisture. Forms are removed after 24-48 hours, and we thoroughly clean the work area.</p>
            </div>
            
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-dark mt-10 mb-4">Decorative Driveway Options</h3>
            
            <p>A concrete driveway doesn't have to be plain gray. We offer several decorative options to complement your home's architecture and landscaping:</p>
            
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 my-6">
              <li><strong>Stamped Concrete:</strong> Patterns that replicate brick, slate, flagstone, cobblestone, and more. Popular for creating a high-end look at a fraction of the cost of natural materials.</li>
              <li><strong>Colored Concrete:</strong> Integral color mixed throughout or surface-applied stains in earth tones, grays, terracotta, and custom colors to match your home.</li>
              <li><strong>Exposed Aggregate:</strong> A textured finish that reveals the natural stone aggregate within the concrete. Popular for its non-slip surface and natural appearance.</li>
              <li><strong>Borders & Accents:</strong> Decorative borders in contrasting colors or patterns add visual interest and define the driveway edges.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary-dark mt-10 mb-4">Understanding Driveway Costs in Port Orange</h3>
            
            <p>Several factors affect the cost of a new concrete driveway in Volusia County:</p>
            
            <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8 not-prose">
              <table class="w-full text-sm">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-secondary text-white">
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Factor</th>
                    <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Impact on Cost</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Size</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">Larger driveways cost less per square foot due to economies of scale</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Site Prep</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">Removing existing driveway, tree roots, or poor soil adds to prep costs</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Thickness</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">5-6" for heavy vehicles costs more than standard 4" residential</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Decorative Options</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">Stamping, coloring, or exposed aggregate adds 40-60% to base price</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b">
                    <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Shape/Design</td>
                    <td class="px-4 py-3">Curved driveways or complex shapes require more labor</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            
            <p>For most Port Orange homeowners, a new standard concrete driveway falls in the $6,000-$15,000 range. Decorative options and larger sizes can reach $20,000+. We provide detailed written estimates so you know exactly what to expect.</p>
          </div>
          
          <!-- FAQs -->
          <div class="mt-16">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                  <details class="group">
                    <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 cursor-pointer bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition">
                      <span class="font-semibold text-secondary-dark pr-4">{faq.q}</span>
                      <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-gray-600">{faq.a}</div>
                  </details>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-1">
          <!-- Quote Form Card -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100 p-6 sticky top-24">
            <div class="text-center mb-6">
              <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-trust/10 text-trust px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold mb-3">
